description: Seen at 10:00 am off of Naval Base Keyport, in the inlet between Burke Bay and Liberty bay.   Whale breeched the surface 3 times, slowly heading north towards the Keyport Pier in the direction of Liberty Bay.
traveling slowly NNW. Very close to shore.
Seen from the Southworth Ferry Terminal travelling southwest along the west side of Vashon Island.

Heading west out of the entrance of Sakonnett River 1 mile out to sea.
Newport Rhode Island 02840, seen from Sachuest Point
Adult and possibly calf traveling East down Hale's passage toward the Fox Island Bridge from Green's point in South Puget Sound.  Lots of tail slapping going on.

Seen between Pilot Point and Point No Point in Puget Sound, WA.  The whale was blowing and diving in about 200 feet of water (depth) about a half mile to a mile from shore.  It was moving north slowly, I watched it for about a half hour from a boat while I was fishing.  At one point it was surfacing within about 100 feet of the boat.  The underside of the tail was mostly white.

In half moon bay in front of Roosevelt Beach, a medium sized  and small humpback (pretty positive because of the fins, but could have been gray whales), were rolling about just outside of the surf zone, maybe 30 feet offshore.
Heading south between Jones and San Juan islands.
